# Notes - The Web Application Hacker's Handbook

1. Mapping the Application

  - Web spidering
    - tools: burp suite, WebScarab, Zed Attack Proxy
    - robots.txt
      contains a list of URLs that a site doesn't want web spiders to visit.
      (sometimes it contains sensitive information)
    - it could be dangerous to run web spiders on some application, because they may contain urls that perform administrative functionalities like delete users...
    - user-directed spidering
